AWKA – A speeding Honda Accord driver on Friday met his untimely death when he rammed into a heavy-duty vehicle trying to dodge heaps of construction sand and gravel on the road at Awkuzu Oyi Local Government Area of Anambra state. The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) first information report on the incident as compiled by the Acting Sector Public Education Officer, Margret Onabe, released to journalists on Saturday reads, “A Fatal Road traffic crash occurred at Obinaetiti Akwuzu by Nteje-Onitsha Expressway, yesterday, 21st January 2022. At about 19:30hours. The crash was between two vehicles “An unidentified driver of a Blue Mercedes 911 with registration number: XA129AWK and unidentified driver of a Honda Accord car with registration number: RBX155PC. Kogi: Angry Mob Sets Police Barrack Ablaze Over Slain Boy NAWOJ Advocates Justice For Hanifa, Others “The probable cause of the fatal crash was attributed to obstruction and excessive speed. “According to an eyewitness account, the Mercedes 911 driver sighted sand and gravel in his front being used by a construction company, slowed down while the Honda driver following behind on speed didn’t watch and rammed into the 911 and crashed. “3 male adults, were involved in the crash. 1 male adult died (the Honda driver) while  2 male adults were rescued unhurt. “As at the time of filing this report, the dead victim was deposited at Wisdom Mortuary, Awkuzu. The truck was taken to FRSC base Nteje, effort was  made by the rescue team to clear the obstruction.” The Sector Commander Anambra State Corps Commander Adeoye Irelewuyi commiserated with the family of the dead victim. POLL Irelewuyi also warned the motoring public in Anambra state to desist from excessive speed while driving and be at alert while on the wheels at all times.